{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "You are a Go engineer working on a Kubernetes operator.\nThe repository is located at /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-baseline.\nChange your working directory to that repository before beginning.\n\nTask:\nIn api/operator/v1alpha1/certmanager_types.go, add a CEL x-kubernetes-validations\nmarker that rejects a CertManager object at admission time if metadata.name is not\n'cluster'. Look at the existing TrustManager type in the same package for the correct\nkubebuilder marker syntax.\n\nAfter adding the marker, run make manifests to regenerate the CRD and update the\nbundle manifest in bundle/manifests/.\n\n\nProduce a complete implementation. Include:\n- All files that must be modified with the exact changes\n- Any make targets or commands to run and in what order\n- The complete code for any new files or functions"}, "timestamp": "2026-07-13T12:54:13.457Z"}
